01:26.790 --> 01:28.810
Hi. We got you something.

01:32.650 --> 01:34.660
Concealer? To help with the bags.

01:34.700 --> 01:36.280
Don't get us wrong, Ms. Corcoran.

01:36.310 --> 01:37.620
I mean, you are still

01:37.650 --> 01:39.850
the most tappable teacher
at McKinley, by far.

01:39.880 --> 01:41.450
You've been looking tired.

01:41.490 --> 01:42.930
Which makes sense.
You're a single mother.

01:42.960 --> 01:45.050
You've relocated. You have a new job.

01:45.100 --> 01:46.500
It's no wonder you've
stopped working out.

01:46.530 --> 01:48.390
Let us babysit Beth
for a couple of hours,

01:48.440 --> 01:50.440
any night your choosing,
for some me time.

01:50.480 --> 01:52.400
Have you ever babysat before?

01:52.450 --> 01:54.460
Mmm. Ask Mr. Shue.

01:54.480 --> 01:55.630
We took care of

01:55.670 --> 01:56.940
his sister-in-law's three demon spawn,

01:57.040 --> 01:58.360
and they were practically purring

01:58.390 --> 02:00.550
by the end of the night.

02:01.830 --> 02:03.550
Please.

02:03.590 --> 02:06.550
You said you wanted us
to get to know Beth.

02:10.870 --> 02:12.610
I got a bee in my bonnet,

02:12.640 --> 02:15.040
and that bee's name is government waste.

02:15.070 --> 02:16.950
Earlier today, I saw a state employee

02:17.010 --> 02:19.460
in the person of one
Verna the lunch lady

02:19.490 --> 02:23.710
throw away 300 pounds of precious,
expired turkey gravy

02:23.740 --> 02:25.650
simply because Uncle Sam said

02:25.650 --> 02:27.550
there were too many weevils in it.

02:27.580 --> 02:31.090
Well, you know what has no
expiration date, voters?

02:31.120 --> 02:33.600
My rage.

02:33.620 --> 02:35.770
I have in my hand the budget

02:35.780 --> 02:38.370
<i>for the McKinley High production
of West Side Story,</i>

02:38.420 --> 02:42.330
a musical about a race war
that glorifies gang violence,

02:42.380 --> 02:45.460
yet still seems extraordinarily gay.

02:45.480 --> 02:48.460
This is a top secret document, Ohio,

02:48.470 --> 02:50.230
and we're opening it up tonight.

02:51.270 --> 02:54.100
$2,004, Ohio.

02:54.130 --> 02:57.270
That's a year's salary for a
public school math teacher

02:57.290 --> 02:59.770
wasted on fake switchblades

02:59.790 --> 03:02.660
and the soft packing
of teen dance belts.

03:02.680 --> 03:06.810
If this nation wants to impress
its future Chinese overlords,

03:06.840 --> 03:09.050
we need to get our priorities straight.

03:09.120 --> 03:11.990
And that's why I encourage every Ohioan

03:12.030 --> 03:15.150
to call McKinley High School
and sing them this song.

03:15.180 --> 03:17.370
"I'm fed up and angry, too,

03:17.410 --> 03:20.740
and I agree with Candidate Sue."

03:20.770 --> 03:24.150
And that's how Sue... sees it.

03:24.170 --> 03:25.670
McKinley High. Please hold.

03:25.710 --> 03:27.590
McKinley High. Please hold.
McKinley High. Please hold.

03:27.630 --> 03:29.060
You can't just cut the musal.

03:29.100 --> 03:31.890
Sue's pom-pom budget is $4,000 a month.

03:31.900 --> 03:34.050
Can't put a price on cheer, William.

03:34.070 --> 03:35.500
I really expected more from you, ggins.

03:35.530 --> 03:37.430
I thought you were a friend of the arts.

03:37.470 --> 03:40.540
William, I'm caught between
a rock and a different,

03:40.580 --> 03:41.740
yet equally hard, rock.

03:41.760 --> 03:42.880
Just this morning,

03:42.910 --> 03:45.580
I was assaulted in the parking lot.

03:45.600 --> 03:47.740
You! My son can't read,

03:47.760 --> 03:49.580
and you want him to sing and dance?

03:51.270 --> 03:53.690
The Clinton years are over.

03:53.730 --> 03:55.580
We're in a recession, William,

03:55.610 --> 03:57.710
that's about to double-dip
into a piping hot

03:57.740 --> 03:59.970
Crock-Pot of voter fury.

04:00.010 --> 04:02.090
And if this school doesn't
learn some priorities,

04:02.120 --> 04:03.580
well, come November,

04:03.610 --> 04:06.340
the voters will gladly teach you some.

04:07.620 --> 04:09.680
What if I can get the money myself?

04:09.720 --> 04:11.510
Ha. Good luck with that, William.

04:11.570 --> 04:13.600
The arts are going down.

04:13.630 --> 04:14.910
Today the musical,

04:14.940 --> 04:16.660
tomorrow the Glee Club.

04:16.850 --> 04:21.839
Next week, NPR and opera and
brunch and Tom Bergeron.

04:30.360 --> 04:31.770
Hi, Santana.

04:31.800 --> 04:33.670
How many solos did you get
in Glee Club last year?

04:33.690 --> 04:34.940
A few.

04:34.980 --> 04:36.340
"Valerie."

04:36.360 --> 04:37.710
And I loved it.

04:37.740 --> 04:40.070
<i>I was also the lips in Rocky Horror.</i>

04:40.130 --> 04:42.490
Listen, if you and I
were in Shelby's group,

04:42.520 --> 04:44.620
we'd get all the solos and the duets.

04:44.670 --> 04:46.630
Our voices sound amazing together.

04:46.680 --> 04:48.840
Plus, it's an all-girl group.

04:48.870 --> 04:50.590
Why would I care about all-girl?

04:50.650 --> 04:52.720
It's all lady power all the time.

04:52.760 --> 04:54.570
I mean, Shelby's a great teacher.

04:54.590 --> 04:56.980
I'm... I'm hitting notes I
didn't even know existed.

04:57.050 --> 05:00.050
She gets me-- what I have to give.

05:00.070 --> 05:01.580
It feels good.

05:01.610 --> 05:03.950
You know, honestly,
I wish I could, but...

05:04.010 --> 05:05.460
somebody's got to look out for Brittany.

05:05.500 --> 05:07.130
I mean, that special
place where she lives,

05:07.180 --> 05:08.670
yeah, it's beautiful, but...

05:08.720 --> 05:10.840
someone's got to help
her cross the street.

05:10.890 --> 05:13.190
I could never just leave her.

05:13.220 --> 05:15.640
Get her to come with you.

05:22.870 --> 05:24.520
You know what, girl Chang?

05:24.520 --> 05:27.290
If you cry every time
someone gets a hangnail,

05:27.480 --> 05:29.300
it kind of starts toose its effect.

05:29.330 --> 05:30.720
It's not a hangnail.

05:30.760 --> 05:33.070
Mercedes was one of
Glee's original members.

05:33.110 --> 05:35.310
I feel naked in here without her.
Yeah, well, get used to it,

05:35.490 --> 05:36.690
'cause without her singing for us,

05:36.690 --> 05:38.050
we're going to have to perform naked

05:38.060 --> 05:39.650
for the judges to vote
for us at Sectionals.

05:39.690 --> 05:42.170
No. I will not let this
setback crush our spirits.

05:42.210 --> 05:43.820
I mean, we have handled worse.

05:43.840 --> 05:45.290
Than losing one of our best singers?

05:45.330 --> 05:47.210
Kind of hard not to blame you, Mr. Shue.

05:47.210 --> 05:49.060
Think you were too hard
on her at Booty Camp.

05:49.060 --> 05:50.380
I blame Artie.

05:50.430 --> 05:52.270
Why couldn't you have just
given Maria to Mercedes?

05:52.310 --> 05:53.500
Because that would have damaged

05:53.510 --> 05:54.800
my integrity as an artist.

05:54.830 --> 05:56.220
Sorry I am late.

05:56.230 --> 05:57.440
I was putting up posters for my...

05:57.480 --> 05:58.730
for my campaign.

05:58.780 --> 06:00.520
Did you airbrush out your jowls?

06:00.530 --> 06:02.650
No. Look, let' stop it, everybody.

06:02.690 --> 06:03.990
So we lost a singer.

06:04.020 --> 06:05.630
So they canceled the musical.

06:05.660 --> 06:06.990
Wait, what? No, no, no, no.

06:07.020 --> 06:08.920
You can't cancel my musical.

06:08.970 --> 06:10.200
Sue cut the funding.

06:10.210 --> 06:11.250
The point is, right now, we shouldn't

06:11.300 --> 06:12.880
be turning on each other. I agree.

06:12.900 --> 06:15.020
I can only speak from my
experience with the Warblers,

06:15.060 --> 06:17.530
but no show choir is just
one person; it's a team.

06:17.560 --> 06:20.370
When we lost a Warbler,
we just replaced him with another one.

06:20.400 --> 06:22.700
Which is easy when your waiting
list has a waiting list.

06:22.730 --> 06:24.630
Dude, I know you're a big deal at Dalton

06:24.700 --> 06:26.880
or whatever, but we
don't wear blazers her

06:26.920 --> 06:29.840
so have a seat--
I'm trying to give a pep talk.

06:29.880 --> 06:30.850
Didn't you just say something about us

06:30.880 --> 06:31.860
not turning on each other?

06:31.890 --> 06:33.430
No, you can't cancel my musical.

06:33.460 --> 06:35.940
Okay? I was considering
changing my name to Maria.

06:35.980 --> 06:38.350
The musical is not canceled.

06:38.400 --> 06:41.080
As for Mercedes, yes,
that is a huge loss for us,

06:41.120 --> 06:43.280
but we will deal with
replacing her later.

06:43.290 --> 06:45.830
Right now, we need to focus
on putting on this musical.

06:45.880 --> 06:46.820
How?

06:46.880 --> 06:49.120
We sell ads in the program.

06:49.150 --> 06:50.390
I figure we can get ten,

06:50.430 --> 06:51.590
maybe 20 bucks apiece for them.

06:51.620 --> 06:54.060
So we'll only have to sell about 200.

06:54.090 --> 06:56.060
Well, I think it's a brilliant idea.

06:56.100 --> 06:58.080
And I volunteer myself
to spearhead the charge.

06:58.100 --> 07:00.100
It'll give me a great
opportunity to, uh, bust out

07:00.140 --> 07:01.330
<i>my Banana Republic Mad Men collection.</i>

07:01.360 --> 07:03.360
Okay. All right. Let's break off

07:03.420 --> 07:05.140
into smaller groups,
figure out who's going to canvass

07:05.170 --> 07:06.820
which parts of the city.
And guys, I don't care

07:06.830 --> 07:08.200
what Sue does or who leaves us--

07:08.260 --> 07:09.630
everyone in this group's dreams

07:09.660 --> 07:11.340
are going to come true this year.

07:11.370 --> 07:12.720
Let's do it. Hey, Santana.

07:12.760 --> 07:14.930
Ready to help out the team?

07:14.970 --> 07:16.880
Yeah, ofourse. Why?

07:16.940 --> 07:18.860
Just checking.

07:24.200 --> 07:25.680
Hey.

07:27.830 --> 07:30.110
Finn Hudson. You know who I am?

07:30.340 --> 07:32.520
I've seen you on YouTube,
losing Glee Club Nationals

07:32.560 --> 07:34.260
after tongue-kissing your
girlfriend for ten minutes.

07:34.320 --> 07:36.210
Uh... I'm a big, big fan.

07:36.230 --> 07:37.670
Thanks.

07:37.680 --> 07:38.810
At ease.

07:40.930 --> 07:44.270
So... who are you?
Me name's Rory Flanagan.

07:44.300 --> 07:46.280
I'm a foreign exchange
stent from Ireland.

07:46.310 --> 07:48.640
And I love everything about America,

07:48.680 --> 07:51.740
especially NASCAR,
your half-black president

07:51.760 --> 07:53.660
and Victoria's Secret catalogs.

07:53.760 --> 07:55.100
Yeah. Cool. Me, too.

07:55.140 --> 07:56.560
I'm staying at the home
of Brittany S. Pierce,

07:56.600 --> 07:59.340
and she thinks I'm a leprechaun.

07:59.350 --> 08:01.330
Yeah, she'kind of like
Rain Man with boobs.

08:01.380 --> 08:03.280
She said if I grant her three wishes,

08:03.330 --> 08:05.630
I can get into her pot of gold.

08:05.630 --> 08:07.060
So I'm pretending to be a leprechaun.

08:07.090 --> 08:09.720
Her first wish was for
an all-marshmallow box

08:09.760 --> 08:10.720
of Lucky Charms. Ah.

08:10.760 --> 08:12.050
I really want to snog her.

08:12.100 --> 08:13.640
I'm still a virgin.

08:13.750 --> 08:14.850
Have you made any friends yet?

08:14.850 --> 08:17.370
Not really, except for Brittany.

08:17.480 --> 08:18.640
I'm really lonely, you know?

08:18.660 --> 08:21.100
I thought America was all
about different unique people

08:21.140 --> 08:22.660
coming together and
accepting one another.

08:22.840 --> 08:24.460
That's a pretty old brochure, dude.

08:24.500 --> 08:27.160
I could really use some more friends.

08:27.270 --> 08:28.460
Would you be my friend, Finn?

08:28.500 --> 08:30.650
Whoa, whoa. It would be an honor.

08:30.680 --> 08:33.340
In America, dudes don't ask
dudes to be their friends.

08:33.460 --> 08:36.159
Except on Facebook, but even then,
it can take years.

08:40.730 --> 08:42.460
Okay.

08:42.600 --> 08:43.289
I'll be your friend.

08:43.380 --> 08:45.310
But first, you got to help me.

08:45.320 --> 08:47.660
One of the best singers in
Glee Club quit recently,

08:47.700 --> 08:49.430
and there's talk of more defections.

08:49.550 --> 08:51.530
You're staying at Brit's house, right?

08:51.560 --> 08:52.930
If you hear anything, let me know.

08:52.930 --> 08:54.760
I will. All right.

08:54.800 --> 08:56.540
Thanks. No problem.

08:56.560 --> 08:57.750
See you around.

08:57.810 --> 09:00.220
Finn Hudson-- that's Irish, right?

09:00.230 --> 09:02.420
Nah. Nah, my mom's from Toledo.

09:06.700 --> 09:08.600
Okay, uh, I got my iPod, my cell phone.

09:08.650 --> 09:09.690
You have my number?

09:09.720 --> 09:11.230
You wrote it on my hand.

09:11.240 --> 09:12.280
Okay. Okay.

09:12.340 --> 09:13.530
All right, honey. I'm going to go.

09:13.570 --> 09:15.070
I'll be back soon,
okay? Give Mama a kiss.

09:15.080 --> 09:17.080
If she gets upset, you just do a little

09:17.090 --> 09:18.340
"Itsy Bitsy Spider." She loves that.

09:18.380 --> 09:20.250
It's okay, boo-boo.

09:20.260 --> 09:21.430
It's okay.

09:21.470 --> 09:23.580
Mommy will be right back, okay?

09:25.370 --> 09:26.640
It's okay. She'll stop
as soon as I leave.

09:26.690 --> 09:28.200
I know she'll stop, okay?

09:28.230 --> 09:29.980
So don't worry. Thank you guys so much.

09:30.040 --> 09:31.610
Okay. I really appreciate it.

09:31.620 --> 09:32.890
Have a good run.

09:32.920 --> 09:34.800
"Itsy Bitsy Spider," guys. It's okay.

09:34.830 --> 09:36.760
Here. Let me take her.

09:36.790 --> 09:38.840
She likes me. (crying stop

09:38.890 --> 09:40.890
It's okay. Big Daddy's got you.

09:40.920 --> 09:42.970
What are you doing?

09:42.980 --> 09:45.060
Proving that Shelby is an unfit mother.

09:45.090 --> 09:47.630
First we plant the stuff,
then we call child services.

09:47.670 --> 09:49.170
Starting in the bathroom.

09:51.670 --> 09:53.320
Let's put you down.

09:54.620 --> 09:55.920
Baby botulism.

09:55.950 --> 09:58.680
Saw this lady on TV who
made her kid's forehead

09:58.720 --> 10:00.600
as smooth as his butt.

10:00.610 --> 10:02.970
People practically lynched her.

10:03.010 --> 10:04.530
You don't think she's going to notice?

10:04.560 --> 10:06.190
She's only sleeping four hours a night.

10:06.220 --> 10:08.610
She barely knows her name.

10:08.650 --> 10:11.360
Baby sacrifice makes me sad.

10:11.380 --> 10:13.520
What's wrong with Shelby eating Mexican?

10:13.540 --> 10:15.240
Is that, like, a boob milk thing?

10:15.310 --> 10:16.880
It's illegal to give
hot sauce to babies.

10:16.920 --> 10:18.300
This mom used to put a drop

10:18.330 --> 10:19.850
on her kid's tongue when he was bad.

10:19.880 --> 10:21.200
She went to jail for a year.

10:21.220 --> 10:23.350
Jail seems a little extreme.

10:23.380 --> 10:24.830
Shelby's a good mom.

10:24.860 --> 10:27.130
Do you want our baby back or not?

10:28.100 --> 10:29.610
Yeah, I do.

10:31.690 --> 10:33.000
Hey, Dad.

10:33.030 --> 10:34.910
I wanted to show you my program

10:34.930 --> 10:36.570
<i>for McKinley's production
of West Side Story.</i>

10:36.580 --> 10:39.520
It's inspired by my
favorite 1920s musicals.

10:39.540 --> 10:40.800
Sounds great, Kurt.

10:40.860 --> 10:43.470
Some reason you're showing
this to me right now?

10:43.520 --> 10:45.900
I was hoping that you
might be interested

10:45.930 --> 10:48.410
in purchasing some ad space
to help save the show.

10:48.440 --> 10:50.620
Save the show? We lost the funding.

10:50.650 --> 10:52.000
We're hoping to sell enough ad space

10:52.040 --> 10:53.240
to cover the cost of the show.

10:53.280 --> 10:54.580
They're only ten dollars each.

10:54.620 --> 10:56.460
And I've already talked to
the Lima Mortuary Society

10:56.470 --> 10:58.800
about buying a couple,
and we... we need about 200.

10:58.980 --> 11:00.770
You fund Sue's cheerleading squad,

11:00.810 --> 11:02.860
but you can't find a couple
grand for the musical?

11:02.910 --> 11:04.390
Figgins, allow me to introduce you

11:04.510 --> 11:07.290
to some friends of mine
down at the Rotary Club.

11:07.290 --> 11:08.800
These are the owners of
Lima's three funeral parlors.

11:08.840 --> 11:12.050
Well, strictly speaking,
mine is a pet funeral parlor.

11:12.050 --> 11:13.790
And mine is a crematorium.

11:13.820 --> 11:16.660
So we also bake and delir
delicious brick oven pizza.

11:16.780 --> 11:19.370
These three businessmen
wrote a check today

11:19.410 --> 11:22.430
<i>to fund West Side Story in completion,</i>

11:22.540 --> 11:23.780
and are now assured full-page ads

11:23.810 --> 11:25.030
in the program for the musical.

11:25.060 --> 11:26.680
I'm a big fan of the show,

11:26.700 --> 11:28.610
just because there are
so many deaths in it.

11:28.670 --> 11:30.550
So, Will, unless I'm mistaken,

11:30.580 --> 11:32.000
I think this means the show is back on.

11:32.030 --> 11:33.960
Burt, I think you're right.

11:34.000 --> 11:35.330
Gentlemen, thank you so much.

11:35.370 --> 11:36.870
Appreciate it. Really
appreciate your generosity.

11:36.890 --> 11:38.150
All right, thank you. Thank you.

11:38.170 --> 11:40.270
Burt, I can't thank you enough.

11:40.310 --> 11:42.060
Hey. Sue!

11:43.900 --> 11:46.350
Just thought I'd let you
know we got the money,

11:46.390 --> 11:47.530
so the musical's back on.

11:47.560 --> 11:49.580
Why, if it isn't Porcelain's dad,

11:49.620 --> 11:51.540
who may or may not have a baboon heart.

11:51.570 --> 11:53.180
I thought I smelled blue collar.

11:53.200 --> 11:54.920
Just so you know,
after the musical's done,

11:54.960 --> 11:57.150
I'm going to organize
as much money as I can

